# Parser results UI

## Data shape

Test Parser API `result` is always `{ vendor_name, invoices: [...] }` (one invoice for single-page PDFs). `parserResultInvoices(result)` returns `result.invoices`; `parsedInvoice` is the tab-selected entry. Multiple invoices show `q-tabs` keyed by `invoice_number`.

## Formatting numbers

- Use `formatLineItemField(item, field)` for line item rows (supports `altKey`, e.g. length → height).
- Dimensions: integers as-is; fractional values up to 4 decimals with trailing zeros removed (`parseFloat(value.toFixed(4))`).
- Money fields: 2 decimal places.

## API calls

Use `postAPI` / `putAPI` from `src/utils/api.js` — no hardcoded `localhost:8000` URLs (Vite proxies `/api` to Django in dev).
